

* saevite_Buffer
  handles text editing and undo

  saevite doesn't really use saevite_Buffers since they don't come with cursors
reasoning for this:
  other applications might want to use saevite_Buffer, it wouldn't make any sense to have mutliple cursors, vi-keys or custom configurations for GUI text boxes, however, it would very much make sense to have those in a text editor, so saevite_BufferWrapper handles that.
  @todo it might be a good idea to externalize saevite_Buffer onto a library and rename saevite_BufferWrapper to saevite_Buffer, as those names make more sense.

* saevite_BufferWrapper
  wraps saevite_Buffer, handles cursors
* saevite_Window
  selects a saevite_Buffer
  handles font size, which font
